15 Georgia companies that engage in financing, supplying, distributing, and transporting are
16 dependent to some extent on the peanut industry; and
17 WHEREAS, the Georgia peanut industry has played a significant role in the economic
18 growth and prosperity of our state, contributing an estimated $2 billion to the Georgia
19 economy and supporting the livelihood of more than 150,000 Georgians.
20 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
21 commend the Georgia peanut industry for its outstanding contributions to the economic
22 health of the State of Georgia and recognize March 2025 as Georgia Peanut Month at the
23 state capitol.
24 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
25 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the Georgia Peanut
26 Commission.
